The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business
 Thursday, March 04, 2004  Business Briefs																								 London, March 3: Reuters today named Niall Fitzgerald, the Unilever chairman and CEO, as its new chairman. He has been a non-executive director of the British news agency since 2003. Last month Fitzgerald announced he would step down from his job at Unilever in September after a 37-year stint. He will take the helm of Reuters in October, replacing Christopher Hogg.																								 London, March 3: Royal Dutch/Shell chairman Philip Watts  the target of an investor backlash over a shock downgrade by the company of its oil and gas reserves  has resigned, the company announced today.																								 New York, March 3: Former WorldCom CEO Bernard Ebbers turned himself in to the FBI today to face charges that he conspired with his chief financial officer to commit the biggest corporate fraud in American history.																								 New Delhi, March 3: Oil India Ltd and Numaligarh Refinery Ltd today entered into an agreement for the proposed Numaligarh-Siliguri product pipeline.																								 Mumbai, March 3: Trading in Centurion Bank shares will resume on the stock exchanges from tomorrow with a reduced face value of Re 1 after the financial revamp.																								 Mumbai, March 3: Ind Swift Ltd will consider issuing global depository receipts at its board meeting tomorrow.
